        "text_PJxJEe": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<h3>You received the Nine of Pentacles because you are entering a phase of self-sufficiency and earned ease. This card comes to people who have worked quietly, consistently, and often independently toward stability.<\/h3><h3>Rather than working in isolation or without purpose, you are redefining your own success. You are beginning to recognise your own value without needing constant reassurance or sacrifice.You are allowed to enjoy what you’ve built.<\/h3><h3>You received this card because your life is stabilising in a way that allows you to choose quality over urgency. The Nine of Pentacles congratulates you on living comfortably in your own space, financially, emotionally, or energetically.<\/h3><h3>On Love<\/h3><p>You will choose relationships that respect your autonomy. Give only as good as you get. Independent as you may be, it is worth considering shouldering the relationship and its weights equally. Allow yourself to be taken care of too. <\/p><h3>On Health<\/h3><p>A good mix of resting well incorporating slow rituals will take your wellbeing far. <\/p><h3>On Money \/ Career<\/h3><p>You have been working hard and working consistently. You will see rewards of this, and soon. It will not just be financial stability that will make you enjoy your 2026. <\/p><h3>How to work with this energy<\/h3><h3>Allow yourself to actively choose quality over quantity. Take the time to travel and make space for spontaneity.  <br\/><br\/>Recommended products<\/h3><ol><li>Sunday Rituals Hair Repair & Growth Oil – Slow luxury care<\/li><li>Berry Picked Bag Charm (Blueberry) – Understated elegance<\/li><\/ol><p>You can find these in our pop-up booth at Night At Orchard, along the outdoor pathway between Ngee Ann City & Ion Orchard between 26-28 Dec, 3pm onwards <\/p>",
            "text_size": "typeset2",
            "secondary_color": false,
            "enable_highlight": false,
            "highlight_style": "marker"
          }
        },
